r of chivalry by its patron napoleon bonaparte in  in  antonio campello pinto de sousa fontes  claimed that the osmth was the continuation of lordre du temple fernando campello pinto pereira de sousa fontes succeeded his father as the head of the order in   in  a split occurred within the osmth when general antoine originally antoni zdrojewski was unexpectedly elected as the new grand master of the osmth at the convent of paris in september  zdrojewski became the head of one faction of the order which he referred to by the french translation ordre souverain et militaire du temple de jérusalem osmtj those loyal to fernando de sousa fontes continued to be referred to by the latin translation ordo supremus militaris templi hierosolymitani osmth in  osmth voted to expel fernando de sousa fonte from the order this resulted in another schism with those loyal to fernando de sousa fonte forming a new organization presently known as osmthregency while the remainder of the organization continued on as osmth now known as osmthkti ordo supremus militaris templi hierosolymitani  knights templar international while osmthktis rituals and traditions are currently based upon those of the historical knights templar according to its website and their present leader grand master patrick rea there is no direct historical lineage claimed by osmth between osmth and the th century templars in  the order was accredited by the united nations economic and social council as a nongovernmental organisation in special consultative status one of over  organizations to hold this status the order is an associate member of the international peace bureau and an affiliate of the international center for religion  diplomacy which was founded by one of osmths members in  osmth was elected as a board member of congo conference of ngos in consultative status with the united nationscitation needed organisationedit the order exists in each country under different jurisdictions in america the order is known a